parameters: To think we'd meet at this place──
I haven't seen you for quite a while,
but you're still as cute as ever.
P-please don't make fun of me...
there's something I want to ask you about...
Kaamos is the name of the leader of
Yes, the ones we fought in Talvirar.
I heard all about it from Muracca.
Thank you for helping protect that star.
About how she plans to amplify the Dark attribute's
influence between the stars to destroy Parlates...
Y-you met her again after all that...?
Yes. It happened while we were separated.
Kaamos's purpose is well known by now.
What relationship do you have with her?
I can't say we never knew each other.
Why are you loitering about like this?
It's because it's a state of emergency
that I'm here. I had to correct the influence
We call them the \C[17]Army of the Night\C[0].
We need to prevent them from appearing altogether.
It's just to buy some time for us.
The Army of the Night appears due to the increase
of Dark influence── In other words,
to prevent it, just do the reverse.
You mean strengthen the Light attibute?
I understand your reasoning, but simply
spreading Light around won't do much of anything.
That is why I prepared this for the occasion!
When you install this device in key locations
where the Dark attribute flows strongly,
it'll ward off the area for a while.
Are you sure you should be this carefree
about it? Don't we also have to put
these things around other stars, too?
Signine is most in danger of collapse, yes?
Ten points to Ino, good job!
Attributes have a compatibility with each other.
Especially when considering Light and Dark,
Ice, Water, and Earth are attuned to Dark,
and of those, Water is closest to it.
On the other hand, Fire, Thunder, and Wind
have a high affinity to Light.
Correct. That is why Signine, the Star of Water,
is most susceptible to the effects of Dark.
On the other hand, Torion, the Star of Fire,
will probably not change at all.
Talvirar's the Star of Ice, too...
However, that doesn't mean we can just
laze around doing nothing all day.
We have to be quick on our feet.
Then I'll ask one more question, then.
I thought of this from the start, but
can't you use your great power to do
The Reason of Undeath was yours, wasn't it?
There are many things it can't do.
You don't look anything less than
I'm just a human── with a little smarts, is all.
If even you have to resort to such measures,
can the one known as Kaamos really be defeated?
I'll go set up the Star Beacons now.
Let us assist you, Miss Tahati.
It's not like we have anything to do.
I'll deal with that later at Ainoa.
Ah, yes, about the Star Beacons...
Regarding where to put it, well,
anywhere around Shuva Ocean is fine.
You don't really mean anywhere, do you?
That being said, I'd prefer if they are
\C[17]placed at a dead end, far away
I'll put mine in places you can't
Why have thou not gone back yet?
I know you asked us to go back home,
but we never said we would do as you demand.
One heck of a smug face you got there.
What doth ye plan to do on this astral body?
We're on an adventure. In the meantime,
we also set up some Star Beacons along the way.
Damn that Tahati, always so redundant.
This is beneficial for your planet, no?
That which I despise most is "change".
Not only has the Army of the Night changed that,
but unrelated ones such as thee deciding to get
involved using that as a pretense...
It disturbs one's peace of mind.
If that's the case, then all the better for us
to cooperate. That way, this will be over
One says that it is a nuisance... Well, so be it.
An understanding shan't be reached, it seems.
One has no intention on interfering with Tahati.
Should ye only assist her in such actions,
Ye shalt not enter, one says.
